CEER:

This repository provides the R-scripts to reproduce the figures of the following paper:

Vezér, M. A., Bakker, A.M.R., Keller, K. and Tuana, N. (2016): "Epistemic and Ethical Values in Decision Analytical Models: Flood Risk Management in Coastal Louisiana" submitted to Nature Climate Change.

The models and data are derived from two papers:
- Jonkman, S. N. et al. (2009a) “Risk‐based design of flood defence systems: a preliminary analysis of the optimal protection level for the New Orleans metropolitan area." Journal of Flood Risk Management 2, 170-181,
- Jonkman, S. N. et al. (2009b) “Loss of Life Caused by the Flooding of New Orleans After Hurricane Katrina:  Analysis of the Relationship Between Flood Characteristics and Mortality." Risk Analysis 29, 676–698.

working:
main.R calls all scripts in right order

Alexander Bakker (SCRiM), July 2016


